<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Strengths (what makes it stand out)</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">LangGraph is genuinely non-trivial. Most students show basic LLM API calls; you're using a stateful graph with ReAct, which signals you understand agentic architecture.</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Three distinct use cases (conversational agent + RAG + tool calling) show breadth, not just a one-trick demo.</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">SQLite persistence means it's not a toy — it has real state management.</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">FAISS + HuggingFace embeddings for RAG is the right production-adjacent choice.</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Weaknesses / gaps to watch for</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">The third feature (extended tool calling) being incomplete is a risk if a recruiter asks for a live demo.</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Streamlit UI is fine but looks "student project" — companies like Barclays/Mastercard/ZS will notice polish.</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">No evaluation metrics (response quality, retrieval accuracy) — hard to defend depth in a viva without them.</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Honest rating: 7.5/10</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">For Mu Sigma or ZS it's strong. For Mastercard/Barclays (more engineering-focused), you'd want the third feature done and ideally a cleaner UI.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">The concept and stack are genuinely good — execution and completeness are what'll push it to a 9.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Want to finish the third feature and tighten it up before placements?</p></div></div></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-start opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-focus-within:opacity-100 pointer-coarse:opacity-100 transition" role="group" aria-label="Message actions"><div class="text-text-300"><div class="text-text-300 flex items-stretch justify-between"><button type="button" data-cds="Button" class="cds-reset group/btn relative isolate inline-flex shrink-0 items-center justify-center gap-1.5 whitespace-nowrap select-none cursor-[var(--cds-cursor-interactive)] aria-disabled:cursor-default data-[disabled]:cursor-default border-0 outline-none rounded h-control font-sans text-body font-medium [&amp;:disabled:not([aria-busy])]:opacity-50 disabled:pointer-events-none transition-shadow duration-fast focus-visible:shadow-focus text-primary aria-pressed:text-accent aspect-square w-control px-0 !text-muted hover:!text-primary" aria-label="Copy" data-testid="action-bar-copy" id="base-ui-_r_2gc_"><span aria-hidden="true" class="absolute -z-[1] rounded-[inherit] transition-colors duration-fast group-focus-visible/btn:shadow-[inset_0_0_0_1px_var(--cds-page-bg)] bg-transparent group-hover/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover group-aria-expanded/btn:bg-fill-ghost-hover inset-0 group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent group-hover/btn:group-aria-pressed/btn:bg-accent cds-btn-squish "></span><span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 "><span class="relative"><span data-cds="Icon" class="transition-all opacity-100 scale-100" aria-hidden="true" style="font-family: var(--font-anthropicons, Anthropicons-Variable); font-feature-settings: &quot;liga&quot; 0; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-style: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; line-height: 1; width: 1em; height: 1em; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-shrink: 0; user-select: none; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 433.3;"></span><span data-cds=