ut let me give you the real picture first.</h2><div class="font-claude-response relative leading-[1.65rem] [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:bg-bg-000/50 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-0.5 [&amp;_pre&gt;div]:border-border-400 [&amp;_.ignore-pre-bg&gt;div]:bg-transparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Yes, do all of it — but let me give you the real picture first.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>What Netra AI becomes after these 4 additions</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Right now it's a RAG chatbot. After these changes it becomes a <strong>full agentic RAG system</strong> — stateful, tool-augmented, deployed. That's a different league for placements.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Should you do it? — Straight answer: Yes, prioritize it over the third feature.</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Here's why:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">A <strong>live deployed link</strong> on your resume beats a local demo every time</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Conversation memory + web search makes it <em>actually useful</em>, not just a demo</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Architecture diagram is the first thing ZS/Barclays recruiters look at in a GitHub README</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">It directly fixes the two weaknesses I flagged — completeness and polish</li>
</ul>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>What to do and in what order</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>1. Streamlit Cloud deployment</strong> <em>(do first — blocks everything else)</em></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Get the live link working and stable</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Without this, nothing else matters for recruiter demos</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>2. Conversation memory</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Use <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">st.session_state</code> for in-session memory</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">If you want cross-session persistence, SQLite (same pattern as your other project)</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>3. Web search tool</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Tavily is already in your stack knowledge — plug it in via LangGraph tool node</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">One tool is enough; shows the concept cleanly</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>4. Architecture diagram → README</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Do this last, after features are stable</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Use Excalidraw or draw.io, export as PNG, embed in README</li>
</ul>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Combined resume line after this:</strong></p>
<blockquote class="ml-2 border-l-4 border-[hsl(var(--border-300)/0.1)] pl-4 text-text-300">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><em>Netra AI — Deployed agentic RAG system with conversation memory, web search tool calling, and PDF Q&amp;A. Built with LangGraph, Groq, FAISS, Tavily. Live on Streamlit Cloud.</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">That's a strong line.</p>
