<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Option 2: VS Code Extension</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Install <strong>SQLite Viewer</strong> extension</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Just click on your <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">.db</code> file → it opens like a spreadsheet</li>
</ul>
