_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Here's the verdict:</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">get_messages</code> is called in <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">loadui.py</code> — not in any LLM node file.</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">That means:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">✅ SQLite history is <strong>real and persistent</strong></li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">✅ Chat history is <strong>displayed in the UI</strong> correctly</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">❌ But history is <strong>NOT being fed into the LLM context</strong> — each query starts fresh</li>
</ul>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>So right now Netra AI has:</strong></p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">📺 <strong>Display memory</strong> — UI shows past conversations from SQLite</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">❌ <strong>No true LLM memory</strong> — LLM doesn't know what was said before</li>
</ul>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>How to fix it — add this to <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">basic_chatbot</code> node:</strong></p>
