te</span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">(</span><span>st</span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">.</span><span>session_state</span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">.</span><span>chat_history</span><span class="token token" style="color: rgb(211, 215, 222);">)</span></span></code></pre></div></div>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Confirm it shows all past messages + current user message in order. Then remove it.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Step 2 — Build history correctly</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">The conversion needs to exclude the last message (current user) from history and pass it separately, OR pass everything together. Let me think...</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Actually — <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">state['messages']</code> uses <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">add_messages</code> annotated with LangGraph's reducer. This <strong>appends</strong> incoming messages to existing state. So if you pass full history every time, messages will <strong>duplicate</strong> inside the graph state.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>This is the real risk.</strong></p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
