<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Without this, the LLM behaves generically with no persona.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>2. Cross-session memory on conversation reload</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">When user clicks a past conversation from sidebar → <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">chat_history</code> loads from SQLite ✅ — but does the LLM actually use that history if user sends a new message?</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">Test this right now:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Have a conversation, tell it your name</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Close and reopen the app</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Click that conversation from History</li>
<li class="font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Ask "what is my name?"</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">If it fails → the loaded history isn't being passed correctly on resume.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>3. Chat with PDF has no conversation memory</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal">PDF RAG still passes only current message. Multi-turn PDF Q&amp;A would make it significantly stronger.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>Polish gaps (medium impact):</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>4. Architecture diagram in README</strong> — still missing</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>5. Screenshots in README</strong> — recruiters judge by README first</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>6. No error handling for empty LLM response</strong> — if Groq fails, app crashes silently</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal"><strong>What to do in order:</strong></p>
